Durban - Two people escaped with major injuries after they found themselves trapped between an armco barrier and a superlink truck following a pedestrian accident on Chris Hani Road (North Coast Road). “On arrival on scene a male and female were found to be trapped between an armco barrier and a superlink truck. “With the assistance of Ethekwini Fire and Rescue Services, the victims were carefully extricated, before being placed onto specialised stretchers for the treatment of neck and spinal cord injuries," said Marshall Security spokesman Kyle van Reenen. The man who is believed to be approximately thirty years old suffered serious injury and advanced life support intervention was needed to stabilize him. "Once stable, both patients were taken by ambulance to a nearby medical facility for further care." Van Reenen said event leading up to the incident will form part of SAPS investigation. KwaZulu Natal police spokesman Captain Nqobile Gwala confirmed the incident and said two people were injured and taken to hospital. "A case of reckless and negligent driving was opened at Greenwood Park police station for investigation," said Gwala. POST 